African Barrick Gold Says Capacity Reduced at Buzwagi Plant

-- B y   D a v i d   W h i t e h o u s e
-- 
2011-05-16T06:08:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-16/african-barrick-gold-says-productiuon-capacity-cut-at-buzwagi-in-tanzania.html
African Barrick Gold Ltd. (ABG)  said that
its production capacity has been reduced at the Buzwagi mine in
 Tanzania  after a malfunction in a mill motor.  The production impact in the current quarter will be about
10,000 ounces of gold, the company said in a statement. The
full-year production outlook at Buzwagi is unchanged, the
company said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Whitehouse at 
 dwhitehouse1@bloomberg.net  